&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Prezzee&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prezzee is a global leader in digital gifting and payments, having sold over 140 million gift cards through partnerships with more than 1,500 brands and serving over 6 million customers worldwide. Our mission is to change lives through the power of giving — leveraging borderless payment technology and innovative digital solutions to help people connect and create memorable moments that truly matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role - Note this is a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 month FTC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account&amp;nbsp; Development Coordinator plays a key role in supporting the growth of Prezzee’s B2B customer base by managing and engaging a large portfolio of existing and prospective accounts. This role combines sales coordination, client engagement, and operational support to deliver a seamless customer experience while identifying opportunities to grow revenue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and proactively engage a portfolio of existing and prospective B2B customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop targeted outreach strategies aligned to seasonal demand, key buying periods, and customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse customer behaviour, engagement trends, and market insights to identify growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and action upsell, cross-sell, and account development opportunities across Prezzee’s product offering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Re-engage dormant customers through structured follow-up and relationship-building activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support day-to-day client enquiries and act as a key contact for account-related support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with customer onboarding, account setup, and product implementation to ensure a smooth experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate customers on Prezzee’s gifting solutions, platform features, and program options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide administrative support including order processing, reporting, CRM updates, and platform guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Sales, Marketing, Product, Customer Care, and Technology teams to support customer success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in Sales or Customer Service is a bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer engagement and satisfaction across managed accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reactivation and growth of previously inactive accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identification of upsell opportunities and contribution to pipeline growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurate CRM data management and clear reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective collaboration with internal teams to deliver a high-quality client experience.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is hybrid role, in office 3 days a week, based in Melbourne CBD.&lt;/p&gt;
