&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Prezzee is a global leader in digital gifting and payments, having sold over 140 million gift cards through partnerships with more than 1,500 brands and serving over 6 million customers worldwide. Our mission is to change lives through the power of giving — leveraging borderless payment technology and innovative digital solutions to help people connect and create memorable moments that truly matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Technical Lead at Prezzee, you’ll drive engineering excellence by guiding a distributed team of developers to deliver secure, high-quality solutions across multiple tech stacks. You’ll combine deep technical expertise with strong people leadership—leading by example through architecture design, hands-on coding, and ownership of CI/CD pipelines and production releases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll play a key role in building and scaling high-performing distributed teams, fostering collaboration across time zones, and ensuring clear communication, alignment, and delivery. Alongside this, you’ll champion best practices, embed a DevOps mindset, and create an environment where engineers can thrive and grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the technologies and patterns we’re working on across our teams:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;React, Typescript and Next.JS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microfrontend architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GraphQL Backend for Frontend using Apollo server.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MicroServices backend capable of over 100 orders per second.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Realtime page performance monitoring (LCP, Total Load Time, etc..) in Datadog&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prezzee is an AWS Enterprise customer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We love AI and are rolling out our custom internal AI agent soon.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll lead frontend performance and optimisation across Prezzee’s web platform, driving measurable improvements in speed, conversion, and user experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Core Web Vitals, page performance, and frontend responsiveness across a React / Next.js stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve bottlenecks across rendering, network requests, and bundle size&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Design, and Growth to optimise conversion funnels and user journeys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and evolve scalable frontend architecture using React, Next.js, and TypeScript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage monitoring and analytics tools (e.g. Sentry, Datadog, GA) to inform decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor engineers and lead technical direction within the squad&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience building and optimising modern web apps with React, Next.js, and TypeScript&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to lead and scale distributed engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven impact improving Core Web Vitals and real-world performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with experimentation platforms, A/B testing, or feature flagging tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement to optimize engineering velocity and code quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong testing mindset across unit, integration, and E2E&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with analytics and monitoring tools to drive decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to influence stakeholders and work cross-functionally with Product, Design, and Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience driving alignment and execution across cross-functional and distributed teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
